  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large clay or ceramic tagine or Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the olive paste and cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant and slightly darkened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the shio-koji-cured olives, chicken broth, parsley, garlic, thyme, cumin, smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook, covered, until the olives are tender and the liquid has thickened slightly, about 20 minutes.",
    "Stir in the lemon juice and honey.",
    "Season the tagine with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Serve the tagine hot, garnished with additional parsley and lemon wedges if desired."
